dismissalText.commentary: Vusi Sibanda run out (Bravo) 96 (144b 8x4 1x6 170m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: on the off stump and fuller in length, driven to Bravo at cover, who fields the ball and lets go of it in a single motion and finds Sibanda well short of his crease at the non striker's end.It was a heavy price to pay as earlier in the day, Bravo had dropped Sibanda on 8 and went through the pain of watching him notch 88 more runs.A good knock by Sibanda comes to an end

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza st †Ramdin b Lewis 80 (92b 7x4 1x6 141m) SR: 86.95

dismissalComment.html: outside off stump and tries to go for one shot too much as the momentum and swing imparted on the shot takes him out of the crease and Ramdin, seeing this whips the bails in a flash and replays clearly show that his leg was dangling in the air as the bails were removed. Third Umpire sends him on his way back as he gets some appreciative nods from West Indian fielders

on the fuller length on the off stump, gets behind the line of the delivery and launches it in the air. An apparent lack of timing does not take the ball beyond long on as Deonarine manning the fence there, takes an easy catch

image.caption: Tatenda Taibu
image.longCaption: Tatenda Taibu portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalComment.html: the ball seemed an exact replica of the ball bowled to Chigumbara and the sequence of events were also the same, just that Deonarine had to run a touch more to his right to complete the catch. Fuller length delivery and the chip shot of it has consumed two batsmen in the over now
on a good length and coming in, Matsikenyeri has a wild swing at it and misses, once the ball crossed him it had only leg stump on it's way and the stump was dislodged .

dismissalText.commentary: Runako Morton c Chigumbura b Price 79 (109b 5x4 3x6 128m) SR: 72.47

dismissalComment.html: on the off stump, and Morton sweeps it hard to deep square leg, Chigumbara who was stationed there for this particular shot and Morton falls into the trap. Price triggers celebrations as this is his first wicket of the series

dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels c Chibhabha b Utseya 62 (71b 5x4 1x6 83m) SR: 87.32

dismissalComment.html: on the leg stump, advances down the track and slogs it to deep mid wicket, where   Chibhabha takes a catch on the run, just on the right side of the rope and third umpire too says that it is out. Samuels on his way back is not happy and still asks the umpires something.

dismissalText.commentary: Devon Smith b Chigumbura 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: what a start ! Smith who is in the middle of a poor form, goes back and defends on the backfoot of a short ball, but misses it and gets hit on on the ribs, and writhes in pain and the ball bounces back onto the pitch and rolls over to the stumps and just knocks the bails off. Smith was shocked to turn around and see the bails dislodged

dismissalText.commentary: Brenton Parchment c Masakadza b Utseya 25 (41b 4x4 0x6 59m) SR: 60.97

dismissalComment.html: on the off stump and on a fuller length, Parchment advances down the track and lifts it to long on, where Masakadza takes a back pedalling catch, there was some confusion as the umpires wanted to confirm if Masakadza had touched the ropes. Third Umpire says it's out and Parchment is sent on his way back

batsmen.shot: off side drive on front foot

commentTextItems.html: on the leg stump, comes down the track and lifts it over long on for a boundary and secures the win for his team

commentPostTextItems.html: Zimbabwe have only themselves to blame for the poor batting in the final fifteen overs, where they lost nine wickets . West Indies -aided by half centuries from Morton and Samuels, and a few lusty blows by Bravo towards the end- win the match by a canter.
With the win under the bag West Indies go into the next match as the series winners and Zimbabwe would be playing for pride.
Good night all, and make sure you join us for the fifth and last match of the series on Sunday

dismissalComment.html: on the off stump and fuller in length, driven to Bravo at cover, who fields the ball and lets go of it in a single motion and finds Sibanda well short of his crease at the non striker's end.It was a heavy price to pay as earlier in the day, Bravo had dropped Sibanda on 8 and went through the pain of watching him notch 88 more runs.A good knock by Sibanda comes to an end

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri b Taylor 4 (5b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 80

dismissalComment.html: on a good length and coming in, Matsikenyeri has a wild swing at it and misses, once the ball crossed him it had only leg stump on it's way and the stump was dislodged .

dismissalText.commentary: Keith Dabengwa c †Ramdin b Taylor 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: set him up for this sort of delivery, outside off and swinging away, Dabengwa gets a faint edge back to the keeper and Ramdin takes the offering gladly

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha b Taylor 1 (3b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: on the middle stump and swinging in, Taylor this time around pushes the ball further upto the batsman  and Chibhabha's stumps are left in tatters.What's more the leg stump has been broken into two

headshotImage.caption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Prosper Utseya b Bravo 3 (4b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: tired of watching the leg stump being tumbled back, Bravo does the double bluff as he bowls one on good length and swinging in, and a touch slower in length, and Utseya goes for a lofted shot over mid wicket, misses it and the off stump takes a walk

dismissalText.commentary: Gary Brent run out (Bravo) 9 (7b 1x4 0x6 8m) SR: 128.57

dismissalComment.html: on the off stump and fuller in length and Taylor defends it , Bravo and Brent have a dash towards the wicket, Bravo kicks the ball onto the stumps as Brent is not helped by the fact that his bat comes out of his hand and he is well out of the crease

dismissalText.commentary: Devon Smith b Chigumbura 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: what a start ! Smith who is in the middle of a poor form, goes back and defends on the backfoot of a short ball, but misses it and gets hit on on the ribs, and writhes in pain and the ball bounces back onto the pitch and rolls over to the stumps and just knocks the bails off. Smith was shocked to turn around and see the bails dislodged

dismissalText.commentary: Brenton Parchment c Masakadza b Utseya 25 (41b 4x4 0x6 59m) SR: 60.97

dismissalComment.html: on the off stump and on a fuller length, Parchment advances down the track and lifts it to long on, where Masakadza takes a back pedalling catch, there was some confusion as the umpires wanted to confirm if Masakadza had touched the ropes. Third Umpire says it's out and Parchment is sent on his way back

dismissalText.commentary: Runako Morton c Chigumbura b Price 79 (109b 5x4 3x6 128m) SR: 72.47

dismissalComment.html: on the off stump, and Morton sweeps it hard to deep square leg, Chigumbara who was stationed there for this particular shot and Morton falls into the trap. Price triggers celebrations as this is his first wicket of the series

dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels c Chibhabha b Utseya 62 (71b 5x4 1x6 83m) SR: 87.32

dismissalComment.html: on the leg stump, advances down the track and slogs it to deep mid wicket, where   Chibhabha takes a catch on the run, just on the right side of the rope and third umpire too says that it is out. Samuels on his way back is not happy and still asks the umpires something.

milestones.description: Masakadza and Vusi Sibanda's 167-run partnership is ZIM's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 161 between Andy Flower and Grant Flower

stories.seoTitle: Sluggish West Indies take the series
stories.summary: A dramatic Zimbabwean collapse, triggered by Jerome Taylor's five wickets, and some sloppy fielding from the hosts allowed a depleted yet trigger-happy West Indian line-up to ultimately overhaul a total of 233 and win by five wickets
